   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">In <ph conref="../../../../Warehouse/Product_Name_Warehouse.dita#reference-9043/product_name"
             class="- topic/ph "/>, all the error messages that are displayed in the UI are compiled in one place so that you can view and modify them based on the requirements. The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Error Message Configurator</uicontrol> form enables you to view and modify error messages in the UI by changing the sentence structure without changing the code.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ERROR MESSAGE CONFIGURATOR</uicontrol> list page, each error message displays the information to help you understand from which module these messages are generated and why these messages are generated.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The following sections describe types of error messages, viewing error messages, and modifying error messages:</p>
